  "id": "phekb-pneumonia-meds",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "pneumonia",
  "name": "Pneumonia - Antibiotic Medication Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find pneumonia patients via empirical antibiotics. Standard CAP regimens: macrolide (azithromycin), beta-lactam (amoxicillin, ceftriaxone), fluoroquinolone (levofloxacin), tetracycline (doxycycline). All antibiotics have **massive cross-indication** with other infections (UTI, skin/soft tissue, etc.) — meds-only queries will be very noisy.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed antibiotics commonly used for pneumonia, including azithromycin, ceftriaxone, amoxicillin, levofloxacin, or doxycycline.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on pneumonia antibiotics.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed empirical antibiotics commonly used for community-acquired pneumonia — macrolides (azithromycin), aminopenicillins (amoxicillin), 3rd-generation cephalosporins (ceftriaxone), respiratory fluoroquinolones (levofloxacin), and tetracyclines (doxycycline).",
    "expert": "I need MedicationRequest resources for any pneumonia-relevant antibiotic. Use these RxNorm ingredient codes: 18631 (azithromycin), 2193 (ceftriaxone), 723 (amoxicillin), 82122 (levofloxacin), 3640 (doxycycline). Combine in a single comma-separated code search. Note these antibiotics have massive cross-indication with UTI, skin infections, etc. — antibiotic alone is a poor pneumonia signal. Pair with diagnosis codes for specificity."
  },
